'''Akam Hashim Rahman''' ({{langx|ar|اكام هاشم رحمن}}; {{langx|ku|ئاکام هاشم ڕەحمان}}; born 16 August 1998) is an Iraqi professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] or [[midfielder]] for [[Al-Zawraa SC|Al-Zawraa]] and the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Akam Hashim |url=https://www.365scores.com/ar/football/player/akam-hashem-87211 |access-date=3 February 2024 |website=www.365scores.com}}</ref>

==Club career==
Born in [[Erbil]], Hashim is a youth product of his local team [[Erbil SC]]. He was promoted to the first team in 2017.<ref name="khaleej">{{Cite web |title=آكام هاشم بديلاً لعطوان في تشكيلة "أسود الرافدين"|url=https://www.alkhaleej.ae/2024-01-02/%D8%A2%D9%83%D8%A7%D9%85-%D9%87%D8%A7%D8%B4%D9%85-%D8%A8%D8%AF%D9%8A%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%8B-%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B7%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%AA%D8%B4%D9%83%D9%8A%D9%84%D8%A9-%D8%A3%D8%B3%D9%88%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%81%D8%AF%D9%8A%D9%86/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9-%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A8%D9%8A/%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%B6%D8%A9|date=2 January 2024|website=www.alkhaleej.ae|language=ar}}</ref>

==International career==
In January 2024, Hashim was called up to the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]] to participate in the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]] after [[Amjad Attwan]] withdrew due to an injury.<ref name="khaleej"/><ref>{{cite web|title=National team player Amjad Attwan was injured|url=https://www.alsharqiya.com/en/news/national-team-player-amjad-atwan-was-injured|publisher=Al Sharqiya|date=2 January 2024|access-date=3 January 2024|archive-date=3 January 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240103161807/https://www.alsharqiya.com/en/news/national-team-player-amjad-atwan-was-injured|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Hashim made his debut on 11 June 2024 in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC second round|World Cup qualifier]] against [[Vietnam national football team|Vietnam]] at the [[Basra International Stadium]]. He substituted [[Mohanad Ali]] in the 72nd minute, Iraq won 3–1.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/687448/|title=Iraq v Vietnam game report|date=11 June 2024}}</ref>

